---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ColorStripe from "../components/ColorStripe.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Bursty Transmissions"
  description="A newsletter from Sune Lehmann – science, ideas, and whatever he couldn't stop thinking about long enough to put down. Roughly once a month."
>
  <h1>Bursty Transmissions</h1>
  <ColorStripe thickness="8px" margin="0 0 2rem" />

  <p>
    In network science, bursty dynamics describes a system with long quiet
    stretches punctuated by sudden clusters of activity. This newsletter works
    exactly the same way.
  </p>
  <p>
    I'm <a href="/about">Sune Lehmann</a>, a professor of networks and
    complexity science at DTU. I write when I have something worth saying –
    about science, ideas, and whatever I couldn't stop thinking about long enough
    to put down.
  </p>

  <div class="kit-form">
    <script async data-uid="91a2bcdb6c" src="https://sunelehmann-com.kit.com/91a2bcdb6c/index.js"></script>
  </div>

  <p class="fine-print">No spam. Unsubscribe whenever.</p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .kit-form {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .fine-print {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
